Answer: You are correct on the sql query. The problem is in the data you're using.

Your data has a column "StuID" in the Student table. That's not the same as the "StuID" in the Has_Pet table. If you are trying to find the id of the pet owned by a student, you will have to join the tables.

\begin{code}
SELECT p.StuID, p.PetID
FROM Has_Pet p
INNER JOIN Student s
ON p.StuID = s.StuID
WHERE s.StuLName = 'Smith';
\end{code}

