Answer: \begin{blockquote}

Is there any difference if I use '*' instead of 'country_code' ?
\end{blockquote}

Yes, because

\begin{code}
SELECT DISTINCT * FROM players ORDER BY country_code
\end{code}

will return all the columns in the `players` table, and a distinct count of `country_code` values, whereas

\begin{code}
SELECT DISTINCT country_code FROM players ORDER BY country_code
\end{code}

will only return a distinct count of `country_code` values.

If you want to retrieve the `country_code` column, then you'll want to use

\begin{code}
SELECT country_code FROM players ORDER BY country_code
\end{code}

