Answer: There are two ways you can get this.  One is by using a `JOIN`:

\begin{code}
SELECT s.section_id,
       s.section_name,
       s.section_description
FROM Sections s
JOIN Transcript_Contents tc ON s.section_id = tc.student_course_id;
\end{code}

The other method is by correlating the query:

\begin{code}
SELECT s.section_id,
       s.section_name,
       s.section_description
FROM Sections s
WHERE EXISTS (SELECT 1
              FROM Transcript_Contents tc
              WHERE tc.student_course_id = s.section_id
             );
\end{code}

