Answer: \begin{code}
SELECT c.course_id, c.course_name, c.course_description
FROM courses c JOIN sections s ON c.course_id = s.course_id
WHERE (SELECT count(c1.course_id)
        FROM sections c1
        WHERE c1.course_id = s.course_id
        ) < 2;
\end{code}

To get a list of course names, you can use:

\begin{code}
SELECT c.course_id, c.course_name
FROM courses c JOIN sections s ON c.course_id = s.course_id
WHERE (SELECT count(c1.course_id)
        FROM sections c1
        WHERE c1.course_id = s.course_id
        ) < 2;
\end{code}

You can also use `distinct` if you want a list of all courses that have 2 or less sections.

