Answer: Use `INNER JOIN` instead of `JOIN` (which is an implicit join and may result in an implicit `CROSS JOIN`)

\begin{code}
SELECT treatment.date_of_treatment, professionals.first_name
FROM treatment
INNER JOIN dogs ON treatment.dog_id = dogs.dog_id
INNER JOIN professionals ON treatment.professional_id = professionals.professional_id
WHERE treatment.date_of_treatment != ''
ORDER BY treatment.date_of_treatment;
\end{code}

