Answer: You want to do a simple group by query:

\begin{code}
select owner_id, count(charge_id)
from charges
group by owner_id;
\end{code}

This assumes that you only want the "cost of the treatment" and not the name of the treatment.  If you want the treatment name, then use:

\begin{code}
select owner_id, count(charge_id), charge_type
from charges
group by owner_id;
\end{code}

